<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-03-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="719" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d719">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Count <persName type="from">Cassini</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-03-30"><hi rend="italic">March 30,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>: By order of my
                            Government, I have the honor to inform your excellency that the
                            following announcement has just been made by the commander in chief of
                            the Russian fleet in the Pacific Ocean:</p>
                        <p>“Any public or merchant vessel navigating waters in which military
                            operations are carried on and detected at night without ship lights on
                            board or by day without a flag, and which, after warning by the firing
                            of a gun, will not show its colors, will be considered to be an enemy,
                            and sunk.”</p>
                        <p>Be pleased, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Count Cassini.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>